Imran Uddin used a keyboard spying device to hack into University of Birmingham computers . 
  He was jailed for four months after admitting six breaches of the Computer Misuse Act . 
  The 25-year-old used the device to steal staff passwords and change his exam marks . 
  He bought the 'shadowing' device on the internet and connected it to a number of university computers . 
  UDDin was studying science at the university and was expected to get a 2:2 degree . 
  He changed his marks on one paper from 57 to 73 per cent . 
 